metadata.name: One Year fxhash !!! #5
metadata.description:
"One Year fxhash !!!" is my a bit late contribution for the One Year fxhash anniversary #fxhashturnsone
I selected vivid colors to convey positive feelings and celebrate the one year happy event of fxhash!

"One Year fxhash !!!" combines a 3D interactive and a 2D (flat) mode. 
Initially starts in 3D mode. Use the "M" key to switch mode
You can use the spacebar to stop the auto animation (when in 3D) and interact manually (zoom, rotate)

Wish a "colorful" happy future full of success!! and need also to say a Thank you to all in fxhash and community !!!

50% of sales (and royalties) will go to Savepakistan

CONTROLS & INTERACTIVITY

KEYS:

- M: Toggle mode, between 3D and 2D (Flat) mode (Try it!!)
- S: Save a png file
- R: Reset - reload (like refreshing the browser)
- Spacebar: toggle 3d auto animation (on/off the auto rotation and zoom)


MOUSE:

Use the left or right mouse buttons to Rotate or Zoom (when in 3D mode)

----

metadata.name: The Binding String #85
metadata.description:
........._____.........
......./+_+_+_+\.......
..|.../+/.._..\+\...\/.
..\|.|+|..|x|..|+|..|..
.\/___\+\.|_|./+/__/_|.

100% code. Typography hand-made by @nathansonic

+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+

Press s to save.
Click the screen to pause the animation.

+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+

This piece explores the interplay of our concepts of communication and the web.

The transaction hash creates the randomization but it’s also the protagonist in this story. It dons the stone and halo as the key for how the blockchain speaks to you.

The transaction hash is brought purposefully into the piece in order to recognize its significance almost as a deity in the generative process. It’s the one thin string binding our real-life experience with blockchain.

+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+

If you want a larger scene with more detail (larger resolution), zoom out using the browser zoom. Be careful as the more you zoom out the more ground elements will be created to fill the scene.

+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+

Pricing - Dutch auction
The pricing is a Dutch auction set at 4 - 3 - 3. 433 is the number of randomized variables in the piece.

Mint amount
The mint amount is 170. 170 is the number of unique elements multiplied by 10.

+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+

The binding string started with a focus on maximizing the possible variations.

This has led to the project having 433 randomizable variables that tweak the scene to create insane variation. A lot of this variation is very subtle, but it’s there.

Random variables: 433 = 281 (rand int) + 62 (rand float) + 90 (Perlin noise).

+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+

The binding string has multiple layered scene elements. Some of these elements interact. Plants are forced back by the halo, elements closer to the central glowing rock reflect more light etc. There are 17 elements in total.

Here are some of the elements that characterize the narrative and aesthetic:
Stone circle
Planets
Plants (trees, bushes)
Fireflies
Animated halo
Glyph text
A smart, fully randomized custom palette creator.
Geometric shapes
Atmosphere scenarios ( day, evening, night, foggy)
Rocks
Mossy-ness
Crystal Geodes
Skewed hills
Ground elements (mud, grass)
Math based lighting
Galaxy lines
Shadow dust

+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+

Extra special thanks to @nathansonic for his support, feedback, and code editions.

+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+

3rd party code used:
Various bits by @nathansonic, including a custom palette creator.
Noisejs - github.com/josephg/noisejs - Perlin noise generator
Twgl - github.com/greggman/twgl.js - A small webGL helper.

+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+-+

metadata.name: Fusion #5
metadata.description:
"Fusion" is my third and somehow "larger" work than previous two contributions for the one year of fxhash #fxhashturnsone
Written in few hours in order to be ready for the one year of fxhash (the last day)

Is an interactive animated work. 
Warning: don't Click on the canvas.. It will.. ok see on yourself  ;)

A graphic buffer is used to draw some 2d shapes which i provide as input to a custom glsl shader 
for further processing and pixel manipulation. All is pure generative code.


Again Happy birthday fxhash!


50% of sales (and royalties) will go to #savePakistan


CONTROLS

KEYS:

- S: Save a png file
- R: Reset center of distortion (first click or click & drag your mouse to set the center position)
- Spacebar: toggle animation (on/off)


MOUSE:

-Click or Click & Drag to set a center for distortion (atttraction, twist, collapse)
-Right click to reset the center (like "R" key)

----
Made with p5js and custom shaders

metadata.name: Sketch F #393
metadata.description:
Sketch is an open-ended series. Works evolve as I code a generative project, sometimes drastically. Intermediate works usually don't see the light of day - they get archived and forgotten. This series is snapshots of different forms along the way - each standing alone, but also part of a larger meandering work flow. The word Sketch implies incompleteness. This project may end up being two works, or it could evolve for years. Part of the joy of generative art is never knowing what's around the corner. I have no set schedule. There may be multiple Sketches released a week, or it could be weeks or months between drops. I have no idea where Sketch is heading and there is no guarantee of cohesiveness from Sketch to Sketch. Color palettes and forms will change as new ideas are explored.

Sketch F(ree). A gift to all Sketch A-E collectors. The underlying grid structure from A-E remains, but more variation on size and distribution is added. Many more color palettes are introduced. Grid size, padding, and colors vary.

metadata.name: Kinetograms #220
metadata.description:
Each Kinetogram traces the movement of a number of simple shapes constrained within a single cell or a grid of cells. Forces are applied to the shapes in the form of attraction, gravity or shaking.

Some Kinetograms are partially or completely reflected, vertically or horizontally, some with chromatic replacement.

The aspect ratio is 3:4. The palettes are predominantly based on found textile patterns.

Press 's' to save a png image. Press 'e' to redraw and export a 4K png image. Note that drawing and physical simulation takes some time.

For interactive use, press 't' to tilt the board and 'c' to clear the board.

Written in p5.js with 2D physical simulation using Matter.js. Developed in and optimized for Chrome.

metadata.name: Layers #29
metadata.description:
It's the first time I really delved into studying about P5JS

I spent the last one collecting generative art and it made my passion for all this just grow, as a collector I wanted to move forward and want to do something more and so developed this project. 

I've been a designer for almost 10 years, an art director for over 1 year, I work all day with design every day, Photoshop and its infinite layers haunt me all day, as my passion wanted to insert something related there in my work so I thought of "layers" and thus "Layers" was born, layers and layers, specifically of rectangles one on top of the other forming the interactions of this work.

5 Styles:

Dunes:
Curves, some sharp and others less so, some remind me of sand dunes.

moiree:
It reminds me a little of compositions with a Moiré effect, forming curves where there is the presence of shadows giving relief.

Arranged:

A style where there is a certain organization of lines, but not perfect.

Strips:

Strips of colors on top of each other.

Harmonic:
It forms flat compositions, they are more organized layers.


17 Color Palettes based on famous works such as paintings and compositions:

"Mondrian - Composition with Large Red Plane, Yellow, Black, Gray and Blue / Piet Mondrian"
"Monalisa - Leonardo da Vinci"
"Portrait - Van Gogh self-portrait / Van Gogh"
"Venus - The Birth of Venus / Sandro Botticelli"
"Memory - The Persistence of Memory / Salvador Dalí"
"Son - The Son of Man /René Magritte"
"Guitarist - The Old Guitarist / Pablo Picasso"
"Canna - Red Canna / Georgia O'Keeffe"
"Drowning - Drowning Girl / Roy Lichtenstein"
"American - American Gothic / Grant Wood"
"Sunrise - Impression, Sunrise / Claude Monet"
"Creation - The Creation of Adam / Michelangelo"
"Girl - Girl with a Pearl Earring / Johannes Vermeer"
"Square - Black Square / Kazimir Malevich"
"Wave - The Great Wave off Kanagawa / Katsushika Hokusai"
"Wanderer - Wanderer above the Sea of ​​Fog / David Friedrich"
"Scream - The Scream / Edvard Munch"

"Layers" uses grains/noises function by Gorilla Sun, thanks for sharing your article with us! Article https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/all-about-that-grain

Created with p5js / Alex Benedith

metadata.name: Swatches #55
metadata.description:
Swatches is the first generative token project by Paul Drzal.

Like photography gels scattered on the light table, the layers combine to create the composition.  A random four-color palette in varying opacities creates your swatch, hand pulled on the screen.

Colors are inspired by the bold stylized drawings of architects Wes Jones and Neil Denari.

Press ‘s’ to save your Swatch.  Zoom out and refresh to save a larger file.

metadata.name: Bound #16
metadata.description:
Our journey consists of events that happen one after the other, and most of the time these are quite linear. The parts we remember and cherish often happen when we change paths. "Bound" is about letting go and being open to events that are unpredictable and thus gaining new colorfull experiences. 

This collection exists of connected rectangles on a tight grid with lines cutting their way through the patterns made with a simple algorithm.

Press s in live mode to download.

Download a higher resolution by adding to the URL:
&density=2 / &density=3 / &density=4

Lammetje November 2022
